    "After World War II, <a href=\"/vandewaalh\">Henri Van de Waal</a> succeeded Martin's two positions in Leiden.": [],
    "Martin published various books and articles on Dutch Painting.": [],
    "His most important work is <em>De Hollandsche schilderkunst in de zeventiende eeuw</em>, published in 1935-1936 (two volumes).": [],
    "His field of research was not limited to the seventeenth century.": [],
    "He wrote books on several Dutch painters of late nineteenth century: in 1915, <em>Albert Neuhuys, zijn leven en zijn kunst;</em> in 1917, in collaboration with <a href=\"/mariusg\">G.": [],
